metadata.name: Petri 1500 #1081
metadata.description:
Petri 1500 is a celebration of reaching 1500 Twitter followers.
As I've grown as an artist what represents that growth but a petri dish, filled with life, finding a way. 

A sillybration of all things fx(hash) featuring some of my recognisable pallets and primatives
along with something new to me - noise and 'realistic' nature sketches. 
All mashed for pure fun.

L to download 1000x1000
S to download 4000x4000

metadata.name: 365 Tentacles #118
metadata.description:
Wow, Fxhash ! What a year !

For #fxhashturnsone I decided to explore how far I could take a simple concept: drawing 365 tentacles.
This turned out to be an interesting exercise, as having a strict limitation seemed to spark more ideas than when having complete freedom. There's a lot you can do with 365 things !

99.9% of primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Key commands:
's' to save a png image
'1', '2', '4' to change resolution
'+', '-' to change rendering zoom

metadata.name: Quiet Summer #92
metadata.description:
It was a quiet summer. :-)

---
Fascinated by moire effect,I tried to make some landscape with only using lines. The color of each building is random, and sometimes the colors are same with each other ( with the background too), and made the image more quiet.
Sometimes, the colors are different with each other and the image are more complex than the other ones. 



made by p5js.

metadata.name: Linetract #22
metadata.description:
Art unites people, the same is also true with Artists.

"Linetract" is a collaborative work of two different artist: @Jolie__Michel and @Uniray_net 
Different backgrounds, different styles, same passion for creativity and Art!

"Linetract" is an abstract composition of simple shapes forms and colors, merged into a final minimal and hopefully aesthetic interesting result :)

CONTROLS

KEYS:

- 1-4: Set resolution from 1x to 4x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

Made with p5js and custom shaders

Collaboration project by @Jolie__Michel and @Uniray_net
© January 2023

metadata.name: The City #250
metadata.description:
// The City //

Cities are the most complex human-made interventions on Earth. The human settlements are growing like huge organisms – and the growth is often impossible to plan, control or limit.
Cities as a phenomenon are with their incredible complexity highly enigmatic structures, that are as fascinating as they are terrifying.

This project is a study of the beauty of complexity.

Each city iteration is an entirely unique structure with unique hatching, arrangement of buildings, heights, sizes, additions and rare items.
The cities are made even more organic by the meticulous modelling of analog ink drawing.

The project is 100% generative. All lines, hatching and dots are generated for each iteration.

As a gesture of appreciation towards our supporters, 20% of royalties will go to the original minter.

Key commands:
Press 's' to save a png version
Press '2' to render at twice the resolution
Press 'b' to remove the colored background before saving

The loading progress is animated, hence the epileptic trigger warning.
Due to memory constraints on mobile devices, rendering uses a lower resolution on these.
-----------

Original concept by @Lax_raven
All code by @r1b2art

metadata.name: WatSplash #9
metadata.description:
Water Splash is a stunning piece of art that captures the beauty and "movement" of watercolors, the piece features multiple drops of watercolors as it falls from a "faucet" and creates a splash upon impact. The bright colors and bold brushstrokes used in the painting add to its dynamism and energy.

Overall, Water Splash is a breathtaking work of art that is sure to impress and inspire.

I hope you enjoy it!

metadata.name: Curtains #11
metadata.description:
Curtains

While learning more about flow fields, as an intermediate step, the first version of this came out.
The artwork creates a set of lines; the first point of the lines are anchors, which can be in a straight line, sinus wave, or tangent function.
The second point is set by calculating the angle from the first using Perlin noise.

The project features 10 different hand-picked color schemes.

Actions:
--------------
Press [s] to save
--------------


Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Flexibility #38
metadata.description:
A circular composition made with the p5.js Perlin Noise. Polar coordinates are used in order to obtain the silk-like texture sometimes induced by the work.

From random numbers and trigonometry, this work has came to life and will help others to have a better life for themselves: 10% from primary + 10% from secondary will go to the Cure Parkinson's medical research.

Hope you admire this work as much as I do,

Carlz, 2023

metadata.name: Clouds over the Mountains #109
metadata.description:
“I'd go as far as the end of a stream or fountain, 
And sit and gaze on cloud rising over the mountain.” 
— Wang Wei (Tang dynasty)

「行到水窮處，坐看雲起時。」
—— 唐·王維

This artwork is inspired by the poem above, and creates a view to “gaze on cloud rising over the mountain”. 
This is also a tribute to the traditional Chinese landscape painting.

⛰️⛰️⛰️⛰️

It takes time to generate. Run on a computer for better experience. 
Student of @Newyellow. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: change is life #22
metadata.description:
Change in nature comes as a smooth routine. The color change takes over the leaves until they fall off. And eventually green Will reappear.
It is not so for humans.
This collection looks up to nature and embraces change. At some point in life, an unexpected crisis may occur, yet it can bring new opportunities. Welcome the learning process. Embrace the growth. Face life and live.

metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #82
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

############

Display resolution scales with window size. Press ’h’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x7500 hi-res image. This may take a few seconds to generate depending on your hardware. Press ‘d’ to redraw the artwork.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022
